<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>
[[ Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
currently has 13 species that are found in the Amazon and Orinoco River drainages and in the coastal drainages of the Guyanas (Armbruster, 2003). 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="braueri">Peckoltia braueri</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BEFF0FA1-F5B1-4107-9BA2-873C8F8C90D7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia sabaji Armbruster 2003:6" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sabaji">P. sabaji</taxonomicName>
are the only species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
that have been described from around the Guyana Shield; however, there are many undescribed species (pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
Of the species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
found in Guyana, one was described as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7A1134F8-5490-4F5E-AB11-28A74070C676" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus braueri Eigenmann 1912:232" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="braueri">Hemiancistrus braueri</taxonomicName>
by Eigenmann (1912) based on specimens collected by Richard Schomburgk and originally reported by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="MÃ¼ller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
and Troschel (1849), one was described as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BEFF0FA1-F5B1-4107-9BA2-873C8F8C90D7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia sabaji Armbruster 2003:6" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sabaji">Peckoltia sabaji</taxonomicName>
(Armbruster 2003), and the third represents an undescribed species that is described herein as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8DCD7B7B-0DD7-44AD-A43B-43B30E655342" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia cavatica Armbruster &amp; Werneke 2005:8" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cavatica">P. cavatica</taxonomicName>
. Previously, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="braueri">P. braueri</taxonomicName>
was known only from the type that was collected in the Takutu River (Negro River drainage), and that specimen had already lost its color by the time it was described by Eigenmann (1912). 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="braueri">Peckoltia braueri</taxonomicName>
has also recently been considered a species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2AC0D766-F761-4436-B6F4-395BBA997694" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus Bleeker 1862:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiancistrus</taxonomicName>
(Cardoso and Lucinda, 2003); however, the color pattern of the fish is more consistent with the species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
. Currently, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2AC0D766-F761-4436-B6F4-395BBA997694" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus Bleeker 1862:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiancistrus</taxonomicName>
are impossible to distinguish and are likely closely related to one another (Armbruster, 2004). In general, species with dorsal saddles and bands in the fins are referred to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
and those with spots or uniform coloration are referred to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2AC0D766-F761-4436-B6F4-395BBA997694" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus Bleeker 1862:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiancistrus</taxonomicName>
; however, this is not a very adequate situation, and the distinction between 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2AC0D766-F761-4436-B6F4-395BBA997694" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus Bleeker 1862:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiancistrus</taxonomicName>
requires much further work. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="braueri">Peckoltia braueri</taxonomicName>
is certainly much more similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vittata">P. vittata (Steindachner)</taxonomicName>
(the type of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
) than to 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medians">H. medians (Kner)</taxonomicName>
(the type of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2AC0D766-F761-4436-B6F4-395BBA997694" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus Bleeker 1862:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiancistrus</taxonomicName>
). We collected 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8DCD7B7B-0DD7-44AD-A43B-43B30E655342" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia cavatica Armbruster &amp; Werneke 2005:8" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cavatica">P. cavatica</taxonomicName>
from two localities around the Macushi village of Massara, and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="braueri">P. braueri</taxonomicName>
in three localities around Lethem. In this manuscript, we redescribe 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="braueri">P. braueri</taxonomicName>
and describe 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8DCD7B7B-0DD7-44AD-A43B-43B30E655342" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia cavatica Armbruster &amp; Werneke 2005:8" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cavatica">P. cavatica</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
